Document Title: Risk Treatment Plan – Kahana Oasis

Effective Date: March 2026
Owner: Security Lead
Approved By: CTO / CEO (Adam Kershner)

1. Purpose
This Risk Treatment Plan defines how Kahana will address the information security risks identified in the Risk Register. It maps each risk to specific mitigation or acceptance decisions, actions, owners, and timelines so progress can be tracked and demonstrated for SOC 2.

2. Scope
This plan applies to:

All risks recorded in the Information Security Risk Register that affect Kahana Oasis and supporting systems.

All teams responsible for implementing security, infrastructure, and process controls.

3. Treatment Options
For each risk, Kahana chooses one or more of the following:

Mitigate: Implement controls to reduce likelihood and/or impact.

Accept: Consciously accept the risk at its current level (usually only for Low/Medium risks), with documented justification.

Transfer: Shift the impact through insurance or contractual arrangements (e.g., relying on vendor commitments).

Avoid: Change plans to remove the risky activity (e.g., not implementing a feature or decommissioning a system).

4. Treatment Plan Template (Fields)
Use these fields (columns) in a table or spreadsheet:

Risk ID (linked to Risk Register)

Risk Title

Current Risk Rating (from register)

Treatment Decision (Mitigate / Accept / Transfer / Avoid)

Planned Mitigation Actions (bullets or short description)

Control(s) Involved (policy, process, or technical control)

Owner (role/name)

Target Completion Date

Status (Not Started / In Progress / Completed / Accepted)

Residual Risk Rating (expected/actual)

Notes / References (tickets, docs, evidence)

